### Adoption Site 2 — `IssueDetail.tsx` plan section (lines 155–164 + 385–395)

Add a local `loadingPlan` state alongside the existing `plan` state. Set it `true` before the `invoke("get_plan", ...)`, clear it in the `.then`/`.catch`:

```tsx
const [loadingPlan, setLoadingPlan] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => {
  if (!work || !activeProject) { setPlan(null); setLoadingPlan(false); return; }
  setLoadingPlan(true);
  invoke<...>("get_plan", { issueNumber: ..., tikiPath: ... })
    .then(p => { setPlan(p); setLoadingPlan(false); })
    .catch(() => { setPlan(null); setLoadingPlan(false); });
}, [work, activeProject]);
```

In the plan-render gate (around line 388), render skeleton rows when `loadingPlan && work !== null`:

```tsx
{loadingPlan && work !== null && (
  <div className="detail-plan-phases" aria-busy="true">
    {Array.from({ length: 3 }, (_, i) => <Skeleton key={i} height={28} />)}
  </div>
)}
{!loadingPlan && plan && plan.phases.length > 0 && (
  /* existing phase list */
)}
```

