### Scope boundaries

- New files: `Skeleton.tsx`, `Skeleton.css` in `components/ui/`.
- Modified files: `IssuesSection.tsx`, `IssueDetail.tsx`, `IssueComments.tsx`.
- Optional: remove now-unused `.issues-section-loading` and `.issues-section-spinner` CSS from `IssuesSection.css` if they're orphaned (or leave them — the refresh-button spinner still uses `.spinning` per line 238). **Verify before deleting.**
- No Rust / IPC / state-store changes. No new dependencies.
- Uses existing `--bg-tertiary`, `--bg-hover`, `--border-color` tokens — both themes adapt automatically.

### Test plan

- `pnpm build` — clean tsc -b + vite. Watch for TS6133 unused imports especially in IssuesSection (if it imported the old `.issues-section-loading` markup helpers).
- `pnpm test` — 89 desktop vitest baseline preserved.
- Manual smoke: (a) open the app on a project with issues → during fetch see 5 shimmering card skeletons in the sidebar, replaced cleanly by real cards; (b) click an active-work issue with a plan → during fetch see 3 shimmering phase-row skeletons, replaced by the real phase list; (c) scroll the detail panel to comments while they load → 3-line shimmering text block; (d) toggle OS reduced-motion preference → all three sites render flat blocks (no gradient stripe visible).
